Norwich were big winners in the Championship as they crushed Huddersfield 5-0 at Carrow Road, with Bradley Johnson bagging a brace and Nathan Redmond, Cameron Jerome and Lewis Grabban all scoring after the Terriers had Murray Wallace sent off in the 17th minute.

Eidur Gudjohnsen appeared as a second-half substitute for Bolton at Macron Stadium, but there were no goals in Wanderers' clash with Ipswich.

Jonathan Douglas, Andre Gray and Jose Ignacio Peleteiro Ramallo struck as Brentford beat Blackburn 3-1.

